      "path": "server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go",
      "function": "rangeKeys"
    }
  ],
  "text": "The authoritative source of the 'mvcc: required revision has been compacted' error originates in the upstream etcd-io/etcd repository, not in Kubernetes vendored copies. The error constant ErrCompacted is defined in server/mvcc/kvstore.go at line 39 as: var ErrCompacted = errors.New(\"mvcc: required revision has been compacted\"). This error is returned by the core function rangeKeys in server/mvcc/kvstore_txn.go (lines 128-137) when a client requests a revision that is less than the compactMainRev—i.e., a revision that has been garbage-collected by MVCC compaction. The check occurs at line 136-137: if rev < tr.s.compactMainRev { return &RangeResult{KVs: nil, Count: -1, Rev: 0}, ErrCompacted }. The rangeKeys method is called by the public Range interface to handle range queries on the key-value store. Kubernetes vendored copies in vendor/go.etcd.io/etcd/ and Kubernetes error-mapping layers in staging/src/k8s.io/apiserver/pkg/storage/etcd3/errors.go are not the authoritative sources—they are merely consumers and translators of this error. The actual error originates from the MVCC (multi-version concurrency control) subsystem in etcd's server/mvcc package."
}

